# Copy this file to `.env` in this directory (client/.env) and fill in real
# values. Never commit the real `.env` file.
#
# VITE_API_URL — optional. The origin the client's API requests are sent to
# (see src/api/client.ts, which builds each request as
# `${VITE_API_URL}/api${path}`).
#
#   - Leave unset (the default) to keep same-origin relative-path behavior:
#     - In dev, Vite's dev-server proxy (vite.config.ts) forwards `/api/*` to
#       the backend repo's server, currently hardcoded to
#       http://localhost:4000 — update that file if the backend runs
#       elsewhere.
#     - In same-domain production setups, Caddy (in the separate backend
#       repo) reverse-proxies `/api/*` to the Express process and serves this
#       client's static build for everything else.
#   - Set it to an absolute origin to point the client at a separate API
#     origin instead (e.g. when the API is served from its own subdomain).
#     This relies on the backend's CORS + credentialed-cookie config to allow
#     the cross-origin requests.
#
# VITE_API_URL=https://anthony-api.isseylab.com
